<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,662,796]" pageId="1" pageNumber="51">
Carl Bořivoy Presl described this species from 
<collectingRegion box="[685,750,662,688]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="1" pageNumber="51">Sicily</collectingRegion>
(“Ad rivulos Nebrodum”). In the Herbarium Presl (
<collectionCode box="[1355,1392,662,688]" country="Czech Republic" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15576" name="National Museum in Prague" pageId="1" pageNumber="51" type="Herbarium">PR</collectionCode>
) is a specimen that conforms with the protologue, can be considered as original material, and is here selected as the 
<typeStatus box="[1349,1452,698,724]" pageId="1" pageNumber="51">lectotype</typeStatus>
since 
<collectionCode box="[200,209,734,760]" country="Romania" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14415" name="&amp;quot;Alexandru Ioan Cuza&amp;quot; University" pageId="1" pageNumber="51" type="Herbarium">I</collectionCode>
was not able to trace further original materials. The 
<typeStatus box="[792,895,734,760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="51">lectotype</typeStatus>
confirms the current application of the name (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pignatti, S." box="[136,289,770,796]" pageId="1" pageNumber="51" refId="ref2232" refString="Pignatti, S. (1982) Flora d'Italia 2. Edagricole, Bologna, 732 pp." type="book" year="1982">Pignatti 1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tutin, T. G." box="[300,426,770,796]" pageId="1" pageNumber="51" pagination="269 - 286" refId="ref2387" refString="Tutin, T. G., (1993) Ranunculus L. In: Tutin, T. G., Burges, N. A., Chater, A. O., Edmondson, J. R., Heywood, V. H., Moore, D. M., Valentine, D. H., Walters, S. M. &amp; Webb, D. A. (Eds.) Flora Europaea 1 (ed. 2). Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, pp. 269 - 286." type="book chapter" year="1993">Tutin 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
